WACKY WEB WEEK
<br><br></font>


<font face="Arial,Sans-serif" color="black" size="4"><b>

Gamer takes a different look at MS Surface
</b><br></font>
<font face="Arial,Sans-Serif" color="black" size="1"><br></font>


<table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="white" summary="Wacky Web Week">
<tr>
<td width="110" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="FFFFFF">
<a href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/19c3e5h/?url=www.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DCZrr7AZ9nCY">
<img src="http://WindowsSecrets.com/images/wsn/W070628-surface.jpg"
align="left" width="110" height="100" border="0" hspace="0" vspace="0"
title="Microsoft Surface" alt="Microsoft Surface"></a>
</td>

<td width="510" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="FFFFFF">

<font face="Arial,Sans-serif" color="#000000" size="2">
The big buzz in sexy new technology lately is 
<a href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/629259h/?url=www.microsoft.com%2Fsurface%2F">Microsoft Surface</a>. 
The concept is to embed a fancy, highly graphical computer into 
a table top.<br><br> 

But not everyone is so excited by the possibilities. 
Among the skeptics are the folks at 
<a href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/d60920h/?url=www.sarcasticgamer.com%2F">The Sarcastic Gamer</a>. 
Check out their twisted trailer extolling the virtues 
(or at least the vexations) of tabletop computing.
<a href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/19c3e5h/?url=www.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DCZrr7AZ9nCY" name="ws_wacky web week">
